## ğŸ“Š Error Handling Consistency

### Error Response Format (MANDATORY)
```javascript
// âœ… CORRECT - Error Handling Pattern
export const controllerMethod = async (req, res) => {
  try {
    // Business logic
    const result = await someAsyncOperation();
    res.status(200).json(result);
    
  } catch (error) {
    console.error('Error in controllerMethod:', error);
    
    // Mongoose validation error
    if (error.name === 'ValidationError') {
      return res.status(400).json({
        message: 'Validation failed',
        errors: Object.values(error.errors).map(e => e.message)
      });
    }
    
    // Duplicate key error
    if (error.code === 11000) {
      return res.status(409).json({
        message: 'Duplicate entry'
      });
    }
    
    // Generic error
    res.status(500).json({
      message: 'Internal server error'
    });
  }
};
```

### Frontend Error Handling (MANDATORY)
```javascript
